To minimize recoil, the slide features a heavy profile which also enhances durability and the grips are Hogue soft rubber wraparound panels that greatly absorb the momentum of the pistol upon firing. Other important features of the 92FS Brigadier include the dovetailed front and rear sights that can be easily replaced by the user. Add to this the legendary benefits of the Beretta 92FS (M9), and you get a variant equally suited for home defense, competition, duty or concealed carry and more. Like the standard 92FS, the 92FS Brigadier is a double/single-action semi-auto pistol that employs an open-slide, short-recoil delayed locking-block system, which yields a faster cycle time and delivers exceptional accuracy and reliability. In particular, the open-slide design practically eliminates “stove-piping” and helps flawless cycling and feeding even after thousands and thousands of rounds. When it comes to dependability even in some of the world’s most extreme conditions, the Beretta 92FS still has no match. Add to this the extra weight of the Brigadier slide, and you get enhanced durability even above these specifications. Regardless of the wonderful reputation it may have, the true test for a tactical pistol’s worth is at the shooting range. The 92 family consistently bests the US military requirement of a 10-shot group of 3” or less at 50 meters (just short of 55 yards). This pistol offers a variety of tactical features that make it equally safe, easy to use and dependable in the holster of military personnel as well as for home or personal defense. Its reversible magazine release lets you use either hand for tactical magazine changes, while its ambidextrous safety-decocker makes it flexible for right- or left-handed persons or for shooters trying out different gripping or shooting styles. Its Inox finish is highly resistant to sweat and corrosion, and after shooting, a tool-free disassembly latch makes it a snap to take the pistol apart for cleaning.

title: For Sale:  Egyptian Maadi MISR S/A AKM 7.62x39
postcontent: Built on Russian tooling, machinery, materials, by trained personnel. Pretty close to an Actual Russian AKM of the era. I'm selling my Egyptian Maadi MISR S/A AKM in 7.62x39. These were the last of the Maadis to be imported from Cairo, Egypt that were worth anything in my; and a lot in the AK commnunity's opinion. Not to be confused with the MISR-10 or MISR-90s; the MISR S/A has all Egyptian parts (receiver, chrome lined barrel & bore, furniture, etc.) and built in Cairo to accept double stack magazines unlike the MISR-10 and MISR-90s which were hollowed out by Century. Century Arms imported the MISR S/As without triggers, sears, hammers (the fire control group), nor pistol grips to comply with 922r. The bayonet lugs were ground down and muzzle threads turned down as a result of the at the time; Clinton Assault Weapons Ban to remove all the scary features. I bought this rifle unfired from the original buyer last year. I have about 500 rounds of TulAmmo 122 FMJ through it. I cleaned it after each range trip with only around 100 rounds each time. Only selling to start my own build of another Egyptian Maadi. Rifle functions perfect and has had zero problems. I'm not interested in ANY trades. CASH only. Rifle will only come with original box, manual, sling, cleaning kit, cleaning rod, RIFLE itself, and one 10 round double stack magazine. 30 round magazines pictured are not included. Buyer must be willing to spend up to $25 for a local firearms transfer fee from a local gun shop. I will not sell in a parking lot deal. Sorry.AKAK47AK-47AKM7.62x39SKSEgyptianRussian

postcontent:
For sale used but in good condition Mission First Tactical Tekko Polymer AK-47 Forend Black and Tapco AK pictol grip. The cover for the lower Picatinny rail is missing.
The TP47IRS is an integrated rail system that replaces the original handguards on the AK47 family of rifles. It manufactured using a specially developed Military Grade reinforced, super tough polyamide, with quick and easy installation and no alterations or gunsmithing required. The lower section of the handguard is installed in the same manner as the original part, while the upper sectionis easily attached using the included (4) bolts. When installed the TP47IRS insures a stable, rattle-free platform that will not alter the zero capability of the optics chosen.Four MIL STD 1913 Picatinny rails, two full length upper/lower and two side rails at just over 2 inches, offer options for mounting Picatinny accessories such as optics, lights/lasers,vertical forward grips, bipods and other rail mounted equipment. The two smaller side rails are easily removed should usage be not be required. The included rail cover can be attachedto the lower rail to maintain the original design profile. Made in the USA and is 922R Compliant.
TP47IRS Features and Functions:- Rigid polymer construction of this two piece handguard provides a lightweight alternative to original- Two full length Picatinny rails, upper and lower, allow individualized accessory mounting options- Two smaller side mounted Picatinny rails are ideal for light/laser mounting and will not hinder natural grip- Simplified installation and unique attachment ensure a mounting system that will hold zero during extreme usage- Lower Picatinny rail cover offers original AK47 profile
